snippet.textDisplay: We’ve had this song since last year, and this version sounds worse than the original. This isn’t me hating, this is honest criticism. Why do rappers continuously do that? We saw this happen with Pop Smoke and Mike Amiri..instead of keeping the track the same as the original unreleased version they changed it and make it sound worse. You can tell that his voice is louder in this version, compared to the original version where his voice matches the volume of the beat perfectly. There are also some moments where the beat continues instead of cutting like it does in the unreleased version.. Sleepy Hallow had the same issue, the list of artists goes on and on..JUST KEEP YOUR MUSIC THE SAME AS THE ORIGINAL! IT’S BETTER THAT WAY!
